    "url": "https://docs.python.org/3/library/doctest.html#module-doctest#doctest.DONT_ACCEPT_TRUE_FOR_1",
    "parameters": [],
    "return_type": "",
    "exceptions": [],
    "description": "By default, if an expected output block contains just 1, an actual output block containing just 1 or just True is considered to be a match, and similarly for 0 versus False. When DONT_ACCEPT_TRUE_FOR_1 is specified, neither substitution is allowed. The default behavior caters to that Python changed the return type of many functions from integer to boolean; doctests expecting “little integer” output still work in these cases. This option will probably go away, but not for several years.",
    "example": "",
